    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing optional fields in F1AP UE Context Setup/Modification Response handling\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP CU implementation was not properly processing optional fields in the DUtoCURRCInformation IE from UE Context Setup Response and UE Context Modification Response messages. Specifically, the measGapConfig and requestedP_MaxFR1 fields were being ignored even when present in the received messages.\n\nThis caused issues when the DU included these optional fields, as they were not being forwarded to the RRC layer for processing. The fix ensures all fields in the DUtoCURRCInformation IE are properly handled according to 3GPP TS 38.473 specification.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_cu_ue_context_management.c`: Added processing for measGapConfig and requestedP_MaxFR1 optional fields in both CU_handle_UE_CONTEXT_SETUP_RESPONSE and CU_handle_UE_CONTEXT_MODIFICATION_RESPONSE functions.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure a DU to include measGapConfig or requestedP_MaxFR1 in UE Context Setup/Modification Response messages\n2. Observe that these fields are not processed by the CU\n3. The RRC layer does not receive the complete DUtoCURRCInformation data\n4. UE configuration may be incomplete, leading to potential RRC reconfiguration issues\n\n"
}